label.value: Observed Area Under the First Moment Curve Percent Extrapolation

value.value: The percent of the observed area under the first moment curve (AUMC) that is extrapolated to infinity.

label.value: Observed Area Under the Excretion Rate Curve infinity

value.value: The area under the excretion rate curve (AURC) extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last excretion rate.

label.value: Observed Area Under the Excretion Rate Curve Percent Extrapolation

value.value: The area under the excretion rate curve (AURC) from the last observed non-zero rate value to infinity as a percentage of the area under the excretion rate curve extrapolated to infinity.
The observed mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity.
A carcinoma that arises from the cervix and invades into the stromal tissue.

label.value: Observed Steady State Volume of Distribution

value.value: An estimate of the volume of distribution at steady state, which is the mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity times steady state clearance (MRTINF*Clss), based on the last observed concentration.

label.value: Observed Steady State Volume of Distribution at Terminal Phase

value.value: The volume of distribution of the terminal phase at steady state based on the last observed concentration.

label.value: Observed Total Body Clearance by Fraction of Dose Absorbed

value.value: The observed total body clearance for extravascular administration, where F is the fraction of dose absorbed.
The observed total body clearance for intravascular administration.
The observed volume of distribution based on the terminal phase.

label.value: Observed Volume of Distribution of Absorbed Fraction

value.value: The observed volume of distribution of the absorbed fraction based on the terminal phase, where F equals the fraction of dose absorbed.
A quantification of the amount of light that is absorbed by or transmitted through a substance.
The percentage of the total dose that is recovered.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the Curve Infinity

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from dosing time, based on the predicted last concentration.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the Curve Infinity by Dose

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from dosing time, based on the predicted last concentration, divided by the dose.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the Curve Percent Back Extrapolation

value.value: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity that was due to back extrapolation to estimate concentration at time zero, based upon predicted values.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the Curve Percent Extrapolation

value.value: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from Tlast based on the predicted value for concentration at Tlast.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the First Moment Curve Infinity

value.value: The area under the first moment curve (AUMC) extrapolated to infinity, based on the last predicted concentration.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the First Moment Curve Percent Extrapolation

label.value: Predicted Area Under the Excretion Rate Curve Infinity

value.value: The area under the urinary excretion rate curve (AURC) extrapolated to infinity, based on the last predicted excretion rate.

label.value: Predicted Area Under the Excretion Rate Curve Percent Extrapolation

value.value: The area under the excretion rate curve (AURC) from the last predicted non-zero rate value to infinity as a percentage of the area under the excretion rate curve extrapolated to infinity.

label.value: Predicted Steady State Volume of Distribution at Terminal Phase

value.value: The volume of distribution of the terminal phase at steady state based on the predicted last concentration.

label.value: Predicted Total Body Clearance by Fraction of Dose Absorbed

label.value: Predicted Volume of Distribution of Absorbed Fraction

value.value: The predicted volume of distribution of the absorbed fraction based on the terminal phase, where F equals the fraction of dose absorbed.

label.value: Stage IB Soft Tissue Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IB includes: (T2a, N0, M0, G1, GX); (T2b, N0, M0, G1, GX).  T2a: Superficial tumor more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  T2b: Deep tumor more than 5 cm in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G1: Grade 1.  GX: Grade cannot be assessed. (AJCC 7th ed.)

A microscopy staining method that utilizes a modified trichrome stain to determine the presence of microsporidial species. This staining technique substitutes aniline blue for the fast green counterstain of the original trichrome staining method and decreased levels of phosphotungstic acid in the reagent.

label.value: Stage IIA Soft Tissue Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIA includes: (T1a, N0, M0, G2, G3); (T1b, N0, M0, G2, G3).  T1a: Superficial tumor 5 cm or less in greatest dimension.  T1b: Deep tumor 5 cm or less in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G2: Grade 2.  G3: Grade 3. (AJCC 7th ed.)
